---
import InternalPage from "../../layouts/InternalPage.astro";
import TableOfContents from "../../components/TableOfContents.astro";
import Accordion from "../../components/Accordion.astro";
import AccordionItem from "../../components/AccordionItem.astro";
---

<InternalPage
	title="ReSound Hearing Aids"
	description="Commonwealth Audiology provides repair and maintenance services for ReSound hearing aids in Georgetown, KY. Contact us to learn more!"
	breadcrumbs={[
		{ label: "Home", href: "/" },
		{ label: "Hearing Aids & Products", href: "/hearing-aids-products/" },
		{ label: "ReSound Hearing Aids" },
	]}
>
	<p class="lead-italic">
		Commonwealth Audiology provides repair and maintenance services for ReSound
		hearing aids in Georgetown, KY.
	</p>
	<p>
		At Commonwealth Audiology, we understand how important clear, comfortable
		hearing is to everyday life. While we do not typically fit ReSound hearing
		aids, our audiologist is highly experienced in servicing, maintaining, and
		troubleshooting ReSound devices to keep them working their best.
	</p>
	<p>
		ReSound hearing aids are known for natural sound quality, reliable
		performance, and thoughtful features that work in harmony with the way your
		brain processes sound. Many models include Bluetooth streaming,
		rechargeable batteries, and app-based controls that make personalized
		listening simple and convenient.
	</p>
	<p>
		If you currently wear ReSound technology, our team is here to help you
		continue hearing and living with confidence.
	</p>

	<TableOfContents />

	<h2>ReSound Hearing Aids We Support</h2>

	<h3>ReSound Enzo IA</h3>
	<p>
		Built for severe to profound hearing loss, the Enzo IA is the world's
		smallest rechargeable Super Power hearing aid. It supports Bluetooth LE
		Audio and Auracast™ for direct public audio streaming. The design is
		durable, weather-resistant, and engineered for clearer listening in
		challenging environments.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Automatic noise reduction for clearer speech</li>
		<li>360° listening awareness</li>
		<li>Lightweight, weatherproof build</li>
		<li>Bluetooth LE Audio &amp; Auracast™ ready</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>ReSound Vivia</h3>
	<p>
		ReSound Vivia uses advanced sound processing and AI-driven adjustments to
		keep speech clear in noisy places. Its directional listening systems help
		users follow conversations more easily while staying aware of their
		surroundings.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Long-lasting battery life</li>
		<li>Durable, weather-resistant design</li>
		<li>Bluetooth &amp; Auracast™ connectivity</li>
		<li>Ultra Focus mode for difficult listening situations</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>ReSound Savi</h3>
	<p>
		One of ReSound's more affordable advanced options, Savi combines strong
		sound quality, comfort, and modern wireless features.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>All-day rechargeable power</li>
		<li>Water and dust resistance</li>
		<li>Bluetooth® &amp; Auracast™ streaming</li>
		<li>Hands-free calling</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>ReSound Nexia</h3>
	<p>
		A premium-level hearing aid built for mild to profound loss, Nexia is the
		first line designed for full Bluetooth LE Audio and Auracast™
		compatibility, allowing direct streaming in public spaces.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Advanced Bluetooth performance</li>
		<li>Auracast™ ready</li>
		<li>Smart 3D app for adjustments and tinnitus support</li>
		<li>CROS compatibility for single-sided hearing loss</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>ReSound Omnia RIE &amp; Mini RIE</h3>
	<p>
		Omnia RIE models are designed for clear speech and natural sound in a
		variety of environments.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Bluetooth streaming</li>
		<li>"Check My Fit" placement tool</li>
		<li>Remote app adjustments</li>
		<li>Built-in tinnitus therapy</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>ReSound Omnia ITE</h3>
	<p>
		This custom in-the-ear line uses ReSound's Organic Hearing approach for
		balanced, natural listening, particularly in noisy environments.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Bluetooth wireless streaming</li>
		<li>Remote support and adjustments</li>
		<li>Tinnitus relief tools</li>
		<li>Custom-molded for secure comfort</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>ReSound Omnia BTE &amp; Power BTE</h3>
	<p>
		Designed for moderate to profound hearing loss, these behind-the-ear models
		offer durable, powerful amplification.
	</p>
	<p><strong>Unique Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Bluetooth® streaming</li>
		<li>App-based controls</li>
		<li>Tinnitus support</li>
		<li>Reliable, comfortable design</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>ReSound Accessories &amp; Assistive Technology</h2>
	<p>
		We can help patients pair, use, and troubleshoot ReSound accessories,
		including:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>TV Streamer 2</strong> – Direct television audio</li>
		<li><strong>Phone Clip+</strong> – Hands-free calling</li>
		<li><strong>Multi Mic</strong> – Better hearing in groups</li>
		<li><strong>Remote Control</strong> – Easy program and volume adjustments</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Older ReSound Models We Service</h2>
	<p>
		Our audiologists continue to maintain and repair many earlier ReSound
		technologies, including:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>ReSound Key</li>
		<li>ReSound ONE</li>
		<li>ReSound LiNX Quattro</li>
		<li>ReSound LiNX 3D</li>
		<li>ReSound LiNX 2</li>
		<li>ReSound Enzo Q</li>
		<li>ReSound Enzo 2</li>
		<li>ReSound Picasso</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		If you're unsure whether your device can be serviced, just give us a call,
		we're happy to help.
	</p>

	<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
	<Accordion>
		<AccordionItem title="What technology levels does ReSound offer?">
			<p>ReSound devices typically come in three tiers:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Level 9 – Most advanced features</li>
				<li>Level 7 – Enhanced performance for active lifestyles</li>
				<li>Level 5 – Essential support for everyday listening</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Our audiologist, Dr. Tiffany Brewer, can help you determine which level
				your current device is and how best to optimize it.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="How can I adjust my ReSound hearing aids?">
			<p>Most ReSound devices work with the ReSound Smart 3D™ app, allowing you to:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Change volume</li>
				<li>Adjust programs</li>
				<li>Manage tinnitus features</li>
				<li>Access remote support</li>
			</ul>
			<p>We can help you set up and navigate the app during your visit.</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="How long do ReSound hearing aids last?">
			<p>
				ReSound hearing aids typically last around 5 years, depending on care
				and daily use. Regular maintenance at our clinic can often extend their
				lifespan.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
	</Accordion>

	<h2>ReSound Hearing Aid Support at Commonwealth Audiology</h2>
	<p>
		While we do not typically fit or sell ReSound devices, we are committed to
		helping you maintain, repair, and optimize the hearing aids you already
		rely on. We offer:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Thorough device cleaning and checks</li>
		<li>Repairs and component replacement</li>
		<li>Troubleshooting for apps, connectivity, and streaming</li>
		<li>Guidance on whether an upgrade may benefit you</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		At Commonwealth Audiology, we believe that your hearing care is a
		partnership, and we're here to make sure your devices support you every
		day.
	</p>
	<p><a href="/contact/">Contact us</a> today to schedule your hearing aid service appointment.</p>
</InternalPage>
